articles.description: Some additional details about the website
articles.contents:
Bio
I am a Master’s of Environmental Data Science Student at UCSB living in Santa Barbara. Interested in the confluence of botany, wetlands, data science.
Education
B.S. in Environmental Science and Sustainable Food & Farming | September 2010 - May 2014
Experience
Biologist | WRA, Inc. Emeryville, CA | January 2019 – May 2021
Vegetation Ecology Intern | National Park Service, Point Reyes Station, CA | April 2018 – October 2018
Research Assistant | Everglades Wetland Research Park, Naples, FL | Aug – Jan 2018
Wetland Scientist/Environmental Analyst | VHB, Inc., Watertown, MA | June 2014 – June 2017
Wetland Field Technician | Midwest Biodiversity Institute, Hilliard, OH | April 2016 – September 2016

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:


summary(cars)
